<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000013#     1#          785#">Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-785</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_13.1-785"/><heading><desig>§ 13.1-785.</desig><title>Election of status after formation</title></heading><bodyText><p>A corporation that was not formed as a benefit corporation may become a benefit corporation by amending its articles so that they contain, in addition to matters required by <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 13.1-619"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-619">§ 13.1-619<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000013#     1#          619#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, a statement that the corporation is a benefit corporation. Any such amendment to the articles of incorporation shall be adopted in accordance with the procedures set forth in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 13.1-707"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-707">§ 13.1-707<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000013#     1#          707#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; however, the amendment shall be approved by all shareholders entitled to vote on the amendment, or if no shares have yet been issued, in accordance with <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 13.1-709"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 13.1-709">§ 13.1-709<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000013#     1#          709#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2011 VA CH 698"><content><span normalizedCite="2011 Va. Ch. 698">2011, c. 698<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2011#000698#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PVT0-004G-K4DJ-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 13.1.</desig><title>CORPORATIONS</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 9.</desig><title>VIRGINIA STOCK CORPORATION ACT</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 22.</desig><title>BENEFIT CORPORATIONS.</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Business &amp; Corporate Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QjA4OEVGODBENzY4NDcxM0IyQzA1OTEwQzVDODRBOUE7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OURBNTNBMkQxMTVENEY5RDkzMDkzRDIzQjBENTNFRjg7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MDQ3M0RFODczN0I4NDg2RjlFRDNFMUNBODRDQTU0Q0E</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem>